Analysis on WeRateDogs tweet Data Archive¶

INTRODUCTION¶

THe report majorly is on report dog rate done via WeRateDogs tweets. The analysis was carried out on three datasets merged as one (twitter_archive_master.csv). These datasets centered on dog rating include an archived WeRateDogs tweets in csv format, image prediction carried out on the archive dataset in tsv format and an API json data querried with the tweets IDs. These data were reasonably cleaned, merged and saved as twitter_archive_master.csv. This presentation below details the findings and insights created from the datasets.

Dog with highest Rating¶

In our analysis we observed that dog named "Sam" has the highest rating. This particular dog has 1,655 retweet and 5,927 likes. Here below is the image of "Sam" which belong to the predicted Specie of "Labrador_retriever". The image of this dog appear to be unique compares to other dog images.

Dog stage distribution¶

The stage distribution of the data as depitch below shows that dogs without stage has the highest percentage of the distribution while floofer is the lowest. The concern here is that dogs that were not categorised under any stage feature has the highest feature. Aside unidentified dog stage, pupper has the highest percentage distribution among the identified stages, while floofer has the least percentage.

Retweet and Favourite Trend in Years¶

From the graph below, the posts of the weratedog handle receives more like than retweet. The likes reach maximum in 2017 while retweet obtain maximum at the first quarter of 2016 and continue to decline . Generally the favourite feature on tweeter is easy to click than the retweet feature that might contribute to the reason why the posts have more likes than retweet.
